The paper deals with the construction of binary optimal linear codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of posets and chains suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The construction of codes via simplicial complexes also suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC). The optimization aspect of the codes suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the use of posets and chains in the construction of codes may also suggest a connection to social networks and graph theory (cs.SI).
